# secrets / env (NEVER commit — compose & server read these; W10 deploy .env carries
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD + APP_ENCRYPTION_KEY). server/.env (sqlite DATABASE_URL only) is already
# tracked from W6 and intentionally left as-is; these rules stop NEW secret files leaking.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
server/.env.local

# encrypted DB backups (M6, deploy/aws-ec2-test/backup.sh): the documented crontab pattern runs
# `cd <repo-root> && sh deploy/aws-ec2-test/backup.sh`, so BACKUP_DIR default `./backups` lands
# HERE (repo root), not under deploy/aws-ec2-test/ — that dir's own .gitignore doesn't cover this
# path. Root-anchored rule so a real deploy host that's a git checkout never risks `git add`-ing
# an encrypted dump (found during the 2026-07-02 restore drill, see docs/DEPLOY.md).
/backups/

